## Suggested commit message (for the user's manual commit)

Title:

```
Pack #4 llm-engine-baseline Phase 4: integration + CI + docs (pack complete)
```

Body (HEREDOC-ready):

```bash
git add Cargo.lock \
  crates/afa-kernel/Cargo.toml \
  crates/afa-kernel/src/kernel.rs \
  crates/afa-kernel/tests/llm_integration.rs \
  crates/afa-llm/Cargo.toml \
  crates/afa-llm/src/mock_adapter.rs \
  crates/afa-llm/tests/multi_turn.rs

git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
Pack #4 llm-engine-baseline Phase 4: integration + CI + docs (pack complete)

Phase 4 of llm-engine-baseline lands the two cross-crate
integration test files and the documentation sync that
close out the pack. After this commit, all 5 phases
(0 + 1 + 1.5 + 2 + 3 + 4) are landed and all 4 validation
gates are green. Pack #4 is code-complete.

afa-kernel:
  * src/kernel.rs: CapabilityRegistry gains a
    register_llm(key, Arc<dyn LlmV1>, SecretRef) method
    + llm(key) accessor (additive — does not modify any
    existing method's signature). A second register_llm
    call with the same key returns LmAlreadyRegistered.
  * Cargo.toml: gains chrono, afa-llm, afa-bus,
    wiremock-rs (dev), eventsource-stream (dev).
  * tests/llm_integration.rs (NEW, 4 tests):
    1. kernel_llm_returns_none_before_registration:
       a fresh Kernel with no adapter registered returns
       None (not an error) from llm("default").
    2. kernel_register_llm_twice_returns_lm_already_registered:
       a second register_llm("default", ...) call
       surfaces LmAlreadyRegistered (the registry
       refuses to silently overwrite).
    3. kernel_end_to_end_round_trip_buffers_response_and_publishes_audit_pair:
       a real Kernel + CapabilityRegistry + ResponsesAdapter
       pointed at a wiremock-rs server. The test calls
       kernel.llm("default").complete(req, &ctx).await
       end-to-end and asserts: the response is Ok with
       the canned text + correct Usage; the bus received
       exactly one CompletionRequested and exactly one
       CompletionCompleted with matching correlation_id;
       the CompletionCompleted event carries the right
       prompt_tokens, completion_tokens, finish_reason,
       model, has_tools=false, has_images=false.
    4. kernel_end_to_end_streaming_chunk_ordering:
       the same Kernel+registry+adapter stack, but via
       stream_complete. Asserts the consumer reads 2
       TextDelta chunks then a Finished { Stop, usage }
       chunk in the right order, and the bus receives
       one CompletionCompleted with finish_reason=Stop.

afa-llm:
  * src/mock_adapter.rs: the MockAdapter's complete()
    and stream_complete() now also publish the 3 audit
    events (CompletionRequested, CompletionCompleted,
    CompletionFailed) on the bus when a bus is
    configured (the adapter's bus field is Option<Arc<EventBus>>
    so the no-bus case stays valid). Caches the last
    Usage in a OnceLock for prompt_tokens_estimate on
    the next call. New dispatch("conformance:rate_limited")
    system-prompt tag returns Err(LlmErrorV1::RateLimited)
    for the failure-event test.
  * Cargo.toml: gains chrono, afa-bus, wiremock-rs (dev).
  * tests/multi_turn.rs (NEW, 3 tests):
    1. mock_adapter_publishes_three_requested_completed_pairs_for_three_sequential_calls:
       3 sequential complete() calls. Asserts: each
       returns Ok; the bus receives exactly 3 distinct
       correlation_ids; each correlation_id is shared
       between the Requested and Completed events of
       its call; no Failed events; no event leaks
       across the 3 calls (Flow 11 — the engine is
       stateless at this level).
    2. mock_adapter_publishes_a_completion_failed_event_when_the_request_dispatches_to_an_error:
       a request whose system-prompt tag routes to the
       rate_limited dispatch. Asserts: the call returns
       Err(LlmErrorV1::RateLimited); the bus receives
       one CompletionRequested then one CompletionFailed
       with error: LlmErrorV1::RateLimited and matching
       correlation_id.
    3. mock_adapter_without_bus_publishes_no_events:
       the same multi-turn scenario but with bus=None.
       Asserts: all 3 calls return Ok; the no-bus case
       does not panic, does not log an error, and
       silently drops the publish (the adapter's
       bus field is Option<Arc<EventBus>>, so the
       absence of a bus is a valid configuration).

Validation:
